The '''Schwarzlose Model 1908'''  was a [[semi-automatic pistol]], designed by Andreas Schwarzlose, released in 1908 in [[German Empire]] and produced until 1911.<ref name="Peterson2013">{{cite book|last=Peterson|first=Phillip|title=Standard Catalog of Military Firearms: The Collector's Price and Reference Guide|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=wWYFAQAAQBAJ&pg=PA34|date=18 October 2013|publisher=Krause Publications|location=Iola, Wisconsin|isbn=978-1-4402-3692-1|page= 509}}</ref>

==Operation==
The Schwarzlose employs a very distinctive [[Blow_forward|"blow-forward action"]] operating mechanism.  It has no slide, instead the mechanism is operated by the barrel being projected forward due to the gas pressure and the friction of the bullet passing through the bore, the compressed recoil spring drives the barrel back, stripping the top cartridge from the magazine, chambering the round, and pressing the cartridge head against the standing breech, which is part of the frame.<ref name="HoggWalter2004">{{cite book|last1=Hogg|first1=Ian|last2=Walter|first2=John|title=Pistols of the World|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=okQH6zFgDtUC&pg=PA279|date=29 August 2004|publisher=David & Charles|isbn=0-87349-460-1|pages=279<U+2013>280}}</ref>

